DATA DICTIONARY FOR GOLD LAYER
  
# Overview

The **Gold Layer** represents the final and business-ready layer of the Data Warehouse. It contains curated datasets designed for **analytics, reporting, and business intelligence**.

This layer consists of:

* **Dimension Tables** – Store descriptive attributes used to analyze business entities.
* **Fact Tables** – Store measurable transactional data such as sales.

The following tables are included in the Gold Layer:

* **gold.dim_customers** (Customer Dimension)
* **gold.dim_products** (Product Dimension)
* **gold.fact_sales** (Sales Fact Table)

---

# gold.dim_customers

## Purpose

The **dim_customers** table is a **dimension table** that stores detailed descriptive information about customers.
It enables business users to analyze sales and customer behavior based on attributes such as gender, country, and marital status.

## Columns

| Column Name      | Data Type    | Description                                                             |
| ---------------- | ------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Customer_Key     | BIGINT       | Surrogate key uniquely identifying each customer in the dimension table |
| Customer_id      | INT          | Original customer identifier from the source system                     |
| Cusutomer_number | NVARCHAR(50) | Unique business/customer number used for identification                 |
| First_Name       | NVARCHAR(50) | First name of the customer                                              |
| Last_Name        | NVARCHAR(50) | Last name of the customer                                               |
| Country          | NVARCHAR(50) | Country where the customer resides                                      |
| Marital_Status   | NVARCHAR(50) | Marital status of the customer                                          |
| Gender           | NVARCHAR(50) | Gender of the customer                                                  |
| Birthdate        | DATE         | Date of birth of the customer                                           |
| Create_Date      | DATE         | Date when the customer record was created in the system                 |

